      "file_path": "openecomp-be/lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-core/src/test/java/org/openecomp/sdc/translator/services/heattotosca/impl/resourcetranslation/ContrailV2VlanToInterfaceResourceConnectionTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "Weird. Whenever you add a constant, think about its purpose. For example: 1) a value is used multiple times and you don't want it become different values because of accidental spelling mistakes (e.g. \"false\"/\"fales\"); 2) you want to change a value in one place so that everyone sees the change (e.g. SILENT_MODE = true); 3) you don't care about accurate spelling, but lazy to type the same long string every time (e.g. UNEXPECTED_ERROR = \"I'm sorry, but some unexpected error occurred. Please see the logs for more details\");",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
